snippet.textDisplay: Excellent series of videos on Coronaviruses and COVID-19. Can I ask, what in particular about MERS, or its mechanism of action, accounts for its high mortality rate in comparison with SARS/COVID-19? The mortality rate is also much more stable across age groups, in contrast to the bias seen in SARS/COVID-19.

snippet.textDisplay: I wouldn't go for mortality rates. Not everyone with it exhibits symptoms or severe enough ones to call for a test. Only ones with more severe symptoms are typically tested so that artificially spikes death rates.
